9\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Andr.\">Andr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1179</biblScope> </bibl> (lyr.). --This sense of <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">miserable</tr_> never occurs in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl>; in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:414\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.414</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:18:13\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18.13</biblScope></bibl>, the sense of <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">headstrong</tr_> should be retained. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n101849.4\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> of things, first in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὕπνος ς</foreign>. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">cruel</tr_> sleep, during which Odysseus was betrayed by his companions, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:10:69\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">10.69</biblScope> </bibl>; and in the phrase <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ς. ἔργα</foreign>, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">cruel, shocking, abominable</tr_> doings, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:9:295\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.295</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:22:413\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.413</biblScope> </bibl> (= <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀτασθαλίαι</foreign> <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:416\" d